# Theme Colors Refactor Checklist

**Goal:** Refactor all UI components to use Chakra color tokens (e.g., `color="primary"`, `bg="muted"`, `color="error"`, etc.) in Chakra UI component props, instead of referencing `theme.colors` directly. Only use `theme.colors` for custom inline styles or non-Chakra elements.

- [ ] Refactor all Chakra UI components to use color tokens in props
- [ ] Replace usages of `color={theme.colors.X}` with `color="X"` where X is a token (primary, accent, error, etc.)
- [ ] Use `bg="muted"`, `borderColor="border"`, etc. for backgrounds and borders
- [ ] Only use `theme.colors` for custom inline styles or non-Chakra elements
- [ ] Test theme switching to ensure all colors update correctly
- [ ] Review all pages and components for compliance

**Why:**
- Ensures theme consistency
- Makes theme switching robust
- Improves code maintainability

**Example Before:**
```tsx
<Text color={theme.colors.primary}>Hello</Text>
```
**Example After:**
```tsx
<Text color="primary">Hello</Text>
```

